dataIdInfo.idPurp: This data set represents the most recent changes for the Marine Hydrokinetic (MHK Development Leases or Planning Areas )
dataIdInfo.idAbs:
To provide spatial information on Proposed and Leased Marine Hydrokinetic Energy Planning and Development including the most recent updates to areas of interest, planning areas, and/or leases for MHK Energy Development

off the United States Coast within Federal Waters.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Lease types can include Commercial, Research, Interim Policy, Right-of-Way Grant

attrdomv.udom: Lease types can include Commercial, Research, Interim Policy, Right-of-Way Grant

attr.attrdef: Type of energy source – wind, hydrokinetic

attrdomv.udom: Type of energy source – wave, tidal, current

attr.attrdef: Effective date of lease or grant

attrdomv.udom: Effective date of lease or grant

attr.attrdef: Length of lease term in years

attrdomv.udom: Length of the operations term in years. Lease terms and their duration are defined in Addendum "B" of the lease. There are three types of lease terms: preliminary, site assessment, and operations. This attribute is the duration of the operations term only, for the length of the other lease terms see the lease document.

attr.attrdef: State(s) task force involved during project planning

attrdomv.udom: If not a lease, then the pre lease category for the MHK area development. Could be RFI, RFNCI, Call Area, WEA, etc.
